---
/**
 * faq.astro — 长尾关键词聚合问答页
 *
 * SEO 战略：
 * 一页吃下 "is xchat free/real/safe/launched/encrypted" 等 10+ 个长尾问题词。
 * 每个问题独立 <h2> + JSON-LD FAQPage，帮助 Google Featured Snippet 抓取。
 *
 * 数据来源：
 * - Elon Musk 公开声明（X / @elonmusk）
 * - Apple App Store 预购页 (id1562466975)
 * - 技术媒体报道（TechCrunch, Engadget, Bangkok Post, Alarabiya）
 * - 截至日期会在下方通过 buildDate 自动注入
 */
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import {
  XCHAT_APP_STORE_URL,
  XCHAT_LAUNCH_DISPLAY,
  XCHAT_TELEGRAM_CHANNEL_URL,
} from '../data/xchat';

const buildDate = new Date();
const buildDateISO = buildDate.toISOString().split('T')[0];
const buildDateDisplay = buildDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
  year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric',
});

/** 问答数据：同时用于渲染和 JSON-LD */
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is XChat free?',
    a: 'Yes. XChat is free to use. X Corp has not announced any paid tier for XChat messaging itself. However, access may require an active X (formerly Twitter) account, and X offers paid subscriptions (Premium / Premium+) that unlock other X platform features unrelated to XChat.',
    keywords: ['is xchat free', 'xchat pricing', 'xchat cost'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Is XChat real? Is it actually launching?',
    a: `Yes. XChat officially launched on <strong>${XCHAT_LAUNCH_DISPLAY}</strong>. It is a real, standalone encrypted messaging app from X Corp, available now on the iOS App Store (App ID 6760873038). iPhone and iPad only on day one.`,
    keywords: ['is xchat real', 'is xchat fake', 'is xchat legit'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Has XChat launched yet?',
    a: `Yes. XChat launched on <strong>${XCHAT_LAUNCH_DISPLAY}</strong> and is <a href="${XCHAT_APP_STORE_URL}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">available for download</a> on the iOS App Store. iPhone and iPad only — Android has not been announced.`,
    keywords: ['is xchat launched', 'has xchat launched', 'when was xchat launched'],
  },
  {
    q: 'When did XChat launch?',
    a: `XChat launched on <strong>${XCHAT_LAUNCH_DISPLAY}</strong> for iPhone and iPad. Android availability has <strong>not been announced</strong>. No beta or release window exists for Android users as of today.`,
    keywords: ['when did xchat launch', 'xchat launch date', 'xchat release date'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Is XChat available on Android?',
    a: 'No. XChat is iOS-only (launched April 24, 2026). X Corp has given no release date, beta program, or signup list for Android. If you use Android and want to stay in XChat communities, your only option today is opening X on a mobile browser (x.com) and accessing XChat group threads via the web interface.',
    keywords: ['is xchat available on android', 'xchat android', 'does xchat work on android'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Will XChat ever come to Android?',
    a: 'Almost certainly yes — Android has over 70% of the global smartphone market, and no serious messenger stays iOS-only long term. However, X Corp has given no timeline since the April 24, 2026 iOS launch. Based on how previous X features rolled out, a realistic estimate is <strong>3 to 9 months after iOS launch</strong>. We maintain a dedicated Android tracker at <a href="/">xchat.directory</a> that updates the moment anything official drops.',
    keywords: ['xchat for android when', 'xchat android release'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Is XChat safe and secure?',
    a: 'XChat is marketed as end-to-end encrypted (E2EE), with forward secrecy and local device-only key storage. However, <strong>no independent security audit has been published</strong> as of the April 24, 2026 launch. This is different from Signal, which has been peer-reviewed for years. If you are a journalist, activist, or need maximum assurance, wait for audit results or use <a href="/vs/signal">Signal</a> in the meantime.',
    keywords: ['is xchat safe', 'is xchat secure', 'xchat security'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Is XChat end-to-end encrypted?',
    a: 'Yes, according to X Corp. XChat uses end-to-end encryption (E2EE) for direct messages, meaning only you and the recipient can read them — not X, not governments, not third parties. Keys are stored locally on your device. A PIN protects message history on new devices. Note: this is XChat-specific; regular X Direct Messages (DMs) are <strong>not</strong> E2EE by default.',
    keywords: ['is xchat encrypted', 'is xchat end to end encrypted', 'xchat e2ee'],
  },
  {
    q: 'What is XChat exactly?',
    a: 'XChat is a standalone encrypted messenger app from X Corp (the company formerly known as Twitter). It is built into the X platform but also available as a dedicated app. Think of it as X\'s answer to WhatsApp and Signal: private one-on-one and group messages, end-to-end encrypted by default, tied to your X account.',
    keywords: ['what is xchat', 'what is xchat app', 'xchat meaning'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Who made XChat? Is it Elon Musk?',
    a: 'XChat is built by X Corp, the company owned by Elon Musk. Elon announced the feature personally on X and has promoted it as a privacy-respecting alternative to mainstream messengers. The development team is part of X\'s internal engineering organization, but specific team member names have not been made public.',
    keywords: ['who made xchat', 'xchat elon musk', 'is xchat by elon'],
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I get XChat?',
    a: `Open the <a href="${XCHAT_APP_STORE_URL}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple App Store</a> on your iPhone or iPad, tap "Get" to download (it\'s free), and sign in with your X account. Android users currently have no way to get XChat — the app does not exist on Google Play.`,
    keywords: ['how to get xchat', 'where to download xchat', 'xchat download'],
  },
  {
    q: 'How to change your XChat PIN?',
    a: `Open the XChat app, go to <strong>Settings → Security → Change PIN</strong>. You will need to enter your current PIN and then set a new one. If you have forgotten your PIN, you may need to re-authenticate with your X account credentials.`,
    keywords: ['how to change xchat pin', 'xchat pin reset'],
  },
  {
    q: 'How to delete messages in XChat?',
    a: `Long-press any message and select <strong>"Delete"</strong>. You can choose "Delete for me" (removes it from your view only) or "Delete for everyone" (removes it for all chat participants). Full chat history deletion is available under <strong>Settings → Privacy → Clear Chat History</strong>.`,
    keywords: ['how to delete xchat messages', 'xchat delete chat'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Does XChat work without a phone number?',
    a: 'Unlike WhatsApp and Signal, XChat is tied to your <strong>X account</strong>, not your phone number. This means you can sign up with just an email or your existing X handle. That\'s a privacy advantage for users who don\'t want to expose their phone number to contacts.',
    keywords: ['xchat without phone number', 'xchat signup'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I use XChat on my computer or desktop?',
    a: 'Not yet as a standalone app. However, XChat messages are synced with your X account, so you can read and send XChat messages from <a href="https://x.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">x.com</a> in any desktop browser. A dedicated XChat desktop app has not been announced.',
    keywords: ['xchat desktop', 'xchat for windows', 'xchat for mac'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Is XChat better than WhatsApp, Signal, or Telegram?',
    a: 'It depends on what you value. We built side-by-side comparison pages to help you decide: <a href="/vs/whatsapp">XChat vs WhatsApp</a>, <a href="/vs/signal">XChat vs Signal</a>, <a href="/vs/telegram">XChat vs Telegram</a>. Short version: Signal wins on proven security, WhatsApp wins on ubiquity, Telegram wins on group features, and XChat wins on being tied to the X social graph (no phone number needed).',
    keywords: ['xchat vs whatsapp', 'xchat vs signal', 'xchat vs telegram', 'is xchat better'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Does XChat replace X Direct Messages (DMs)?',
    a: 'Not replace — extend. Regular X DMs still exist and are <strong>not</strong> end-to-end encrypted by default. XChat is the encrypted layer on top, for conversations where privacy matters. You can choose whether a given chat is a regular DM or an XChat encrypted thread.',
    keywords: ['xchat vs x dm', 'xchat direct message'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Does XChat have video calls?',
    a: 'Yes. Video calls were included in the April 24, 2026 launch. Both one-on-one and group video calls are supported, with end-to-end encryption applied to the audio and video streams.',
    keywords: ['xchat video calls', 'xchat video chat', 'does xchat have video'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Does XChat have disappearing messages?',
    a: 'Yes. Disappearing messages shipped with the launch. You can set messages to auto-delete after a chosen duration in any chat. Screenshots are also blocked with notifications sent if someone tries to capture your messages.',
    keywords: ['xchat disappearing messages', 'xchat self destruct', 'xchat vanish mode'],
  },
  {
    q: 'Does XChat support CarPlay?',
    a: 'No. CarPlay support has <strong>not been announced</strong> as of the April 24, 2026 launch. XChat is currently an iPhone/iPad app only; in-car messaging integration may arrive in future updates.',
    keywords: ['xchat carplay', 'xchat apple carplay', 'xchat car'],
  },
  {
    q: 'How do XChat group invite links work?',
    a: 'XChat uses joinable group links similar to WhatsApp and Telegram. A group admin generates an invite link (or QR code) and shares it. Anyone with an X account who clicks the link can request to join. Admins approve or decline requests. <a href="/groups">Browse public XChat groups here</a>.',
    keywords: ['xchat group link', 'xchat invite link', 'how to join xchat group'],
  },
];

/* JSON-LD: FAQPage schema — 让 Google 把每个问答独立显示为 Featured Snippet */
const faqJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: faqs.map((faq) => ({
    '@type': 'Question',
    name: faq.q,
    acceptedAnswer: {
      '@type': 'Answer',
      text: faq.a.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, ''), // 纯文本版本给 schema
    },
  })),
};
---

<Layout
  title="XChat FAQ — Is It Free, Safe, Launched? Every Answer | XChat Hub"
  description="Comprehensive XChat FAQ: is it free? is it safe? has it launched? Android availability, PIN help, encryption, comparison. All answers sourced from official X Corp statements and verified reporting."
  jsonLd={faqJsonLd}
  canonicalPath="/faq"
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', url: 'https://xchat.directory/' },
    { name: 'FAQ', url: 'https://xchat.directory/faq/' },
  ]}
>
  <!-- ==================== HEADER ==================== -->
  <section class="section faq-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">XChat Questions, Answered</span>
      <h1>
        Every XChat Question
        <span class="text-gradient">We Could Find.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead text-secondary prose-body">
        Compiled from official X Corp announcements, App Store metadata, and verified tech reporting. Last reviewed <time datetime={buildDateISO}>{buildDateDisplay}</time> — we update the moment anything changes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== FAQ LIST ==================== -->
  <section class="section-sm">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-page-list">
        {faqs.map((faq, i) => (
          <article class="faq-item" id={`q${i + 1}`}>
            <h2 class="faq-q">{faq.q}</h2>
            <div class="faq-a text-secondary prose-body" set:html={faq.a} />
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== FINAL CTA ==================== -->
  <section class="section final-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="final-card">
        <h2>Didn't Find Your Question?</h2>
        <p class="text-secondary prose-body">
          Drop it in our Telegram community — real humans, real answers, usually within a few hours. We update this page weekly based on what you ask.
        </p>
        <a href="https://t.me/Xchathubcommunity" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
          <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M11.944 0A12 12 0 0 0 0 12a12 12 0 0 0 12 12 12 12 0 0 0 12-12A12 12 0 0 0 12 0a12 12 0 0 0-.056 0zm4.962 7.224c.1-.002.321.023.465.14a.506.506 0 0 1 .171.325c.016.093.036.306.02.472-.18 1.898-.962 6.502-1.36 8.627-.168.9-.499 1.201-.82 1.23-.696.065-1.225-.46-1.9-.902-1.056-.693-1.653-1.124-2.678-1.8-1.185-.78-.417-1.21.258-1.91.177-.184 3.247-2.977 3.307-3.23.007-.032.014-.15-.056-.212s-.174-.041-.249-.024c-.106.024-1.793 1.14-5.061 3.345-.48.33-.913.49-1.302.48-.428-.008-1.252-.241-1.865-.44-.752-.245-1.349-.374-1.297-.789.027-.216.325-.437.893-.663 3.498-1.524 5.83-2.529 6.998-3.014 3.332-1.386 4.025-1.627 4.476-1.635z"/>
          </svg>
          Ask on Telegram
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* ---- Hero ---- */
  .faq-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: 6rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-light);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding: 0.3125rem 0.875rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(29, 155, 240, 0.25);
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: rgba(29, 155, 240, 0.05);
  }

  .faq-hero h1 {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-hero h1 .text-gradient {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.1em;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* ---- FAQ List (独立段落，非折叠 — 每个 Q 都是静态 h2，利于 Google Featured Snippet) ---- */
  .faq-page-list {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item {
    scroll-margin-top: 6rem; /* 锚点跳转时给 sticky header 留空间 */
  }

  .faq-q {
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
  }

  .faq-a {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .faq-a a {
    color: var(--accent-light);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .faq-a strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* ---- Final CTA ---- */
  .final-section {
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .final-card {
    max-width: 640px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    text-align: center;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at top, rgba(29, 155, 240, 0.05), transparent 60%),
      var(--bg-card);
  }

  .final-card h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* ---- Responsive ---- */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .faq-hero { padding-top: 4rem; }
    .faq-page-list { gap: 2rem; }
    .faq-q { font-size: 1.1875rem; }
  }
</style>
